document_title: Warts on the feet (soles): Causes, signs, prevention
subsection_content:
Foot warts are small, flat or rough papules on the feet, often appearing on the instep and heel (areas that experience the most pressure when moving). Foot warts are caused by HPV entering through small cuts or tears on the bottom of the foot. (first)
Most plantar warts are not a serious health problem and usually go away without treatment, especially in children under 12 years old. Although not a deadly disease, warts on the feet need to be treated thoroughly to avoid causing discomfort, pain and reducing quality of life.
